Description: Nine fragments of damaged or unfinished goldwork and jewellery made of embossed gold -foils : setting for a cabochon, earring (?), beads, etc.
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Tell Dafana, From the denuded surface of the site or the neighbourhood ?
Curator's comments: On fragments of goldwork, see W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 76 § 74 : "Among the multitude of fragments of goldwork picked up by the Bedawin who hunt over the denuded surface of the site, were some important scraps bearing on the manufacture of these articles at the place (...); further a piece of gold-foil, cut into the form for making one of the hollow rings (such as pl. xli. 2)..."
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 76 § 74)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.84, p.186, pl.28)
Additional IDs: Miscellaneous number: 1888,02080.169 (incorrect number given on p.186 of Leclère and Spencer 2014)
